-- Turkey Stocks: Bank Asya, Marshall Boya, Teknosa, Zorlu Enerji
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-17T15:11:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/turkey-stocks-bank-asya-marshall-boya-teknosa-zorlu-enerji.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 1.3 percent to 57,331.17 at the close in Istanbul.
Banking shares led declines, with the  banking index  dropping 2.9
percent to its lowest since Jan. 25.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Asya Katilim Bankasi AS (ASYAB)  , an Islamic bank,
dropped 3.5 percent to 1.64 liras, its lowest since Jan. 23.
Brokerage FinansInvest cut the shares to the equivalent of hold,
saying the bank “continues to disappoint investors with its
poor risk management” and its “problematic loan stock
continues to grow.”  Marshall Boya & Vernik Sanayii AS (MRSHL)  , a
manufacturer of paint and other coatings, gained the most since
April 20, adding 5.7 percent to 55.75 liras, after saying it won
a 21.1 million lira ($11.6 million) auction from the Turkish
highways authority.  Teknosa Ic & Dis Ticaret AS (TKNSA)  , a Turkish
electronics retailer owned by  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL) ,
slumped on the first day of trading on the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange , losing 2.2 percent to 7.58 liras. Sabanci sold an 11.5
percent stake in the company in an initial public offering last
week.  Zorlu Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS (ZOREN)  , a Turkish
utility, jumped 2.6 percent to 1.19 liras after reporting a
first-quarter profit of 100.5 million liras ($55 million) which
exceeded analysts’ estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
